<br>
So you are saying if i am 60 with resists i will never take AE damage?  cuz otherwise the scenario is still intact.  I WAS 60 with resists (even tested various levels of resists) and still took damage from AE in HOT.  I was typically put into caster groups (of 59's and 60's) and expected to keep them alive.  Most of the time I did ok.  BUT i slowed down pulling alot (when i mana was actually taken into account =P  otherwise I could jsut say in guild &quot;XXX needs a heal&quot; or &quot;XXX is down&quot;), because I was constantly low of mana, trying to keep five casters alive (and myself).  Throw in a melee (sometimes there arent enough clerics to take all melee) that is taking constant AE damage AND sometimes getting hit (even the best sometimes take a hit occasionally) and I was always lom.  This is given an AE situation, not even considering debuffs.  Lots of times, I was the main healer for a caster group and we were just fighting  melee type mobs.  In those cases I could do ok as long as the casters didnt get summoned.  Then it's bye bye caster-of course that would probably happen with a cleric too.  <br>
<br>
I think alot of people's point is that Druids are a *priest* class-we shouldnt be relegated to just heal casters in EVERY scenario.  We should have a legitimate ability to heal some melee (not MT) in given encounters.  <br>
<br>
/shrug just my personal experience. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukyria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kyria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.vic.com/~paladin/sword.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/11/02 4:14:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=583>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:AE damage</span><hr size=1> No, I am not saying that you will not take AE damage...but your whole group should NOT be all taking damage at the same time where a group heal would be of most benefit.  Yes, we'll all still take AE damage occassionally, but most healers (yes, including druids) should be able to keep up if you are equipped for the fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidonrufflefuzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidon Rufflefuzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Hobbit of Love</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/11/02 11:41:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=597>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raiding</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I'm failing to see why druids are required to heal multiple tanks 4500hp. That's not their job. I'm failing to see why you are required to heal massive AoE damage...you shouldn't be taking it. <br>
